During a press briefing, Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro Mayorkas provided an update on the situation at the border and the recent migrant crisis in Del Rio, Texas. He stated that the number of migrants in Del Rio has significantly decreased and that all migrants have been removed from the camp under the Del Rio International Bridge. Mayorkas also addressed the images of Border Patrol agents on horseback and the investigation into their actions, stating that the department does not tolerate mistreatment of migrants and that the investigation will determine the facts and any necessary consequences. He discussed the operational response to the crisis, including the provision of humanitarian aid and the processing of migrants in accordance with existing laws and procedures. Mayorkas emphasized the need for comprehensive immigration reform and the administration's efforts to address the root causes of migration.